<br>
My take on the state of SWG for launch is that it is a good design that will be a very good game... in about 3 months.<br>
<br>
The character design is absolutely wonderful. You can customize your character to an unprecedented degree; shape of the head, eyes, nose, chin, mouth, age, height, weight, muscularity, skin color, hairstyle, eye color, eye size, etc Even an upper torso slider for the women, so that you dont have to be so ..er.. heroic in proportions. The settings are specific for your gender and species, and it is entirely possible to look nothing like anyone else on your server.<br>
<br>
Mal is correct that they have given us a lot of tools for rp. There are a huge number of emotes (with animations) and character moods (angry, alert, tired, etc.). I have grown to like the chat bubbles, simply because I can still see the avatar I am talking to. No more just focusing on a chat window and never watching the avatar. The entertainer classes actually work in the game world. I have very much enjoyed going to a cantina and watching the dancers and musicians. Very social and a large band with a dance troupe is something worth making a special trip to go see.<br>
<br>
I mostly like the skill system as opposed to EQs class system. The way the skill trees and skill costs are organized makes SWG a pseudo-class based system with no restrictions based on species at all. Some species character stats are better suited to some professions than others, but the stats can be set by the player at character creation AND after playing in the world.<br>
<br>
Because you can also give up learned skills and change your stats (over time) there is really never a need to re-roll unless you want to change your species or your gender. Even your characters appearance can be completely changed by other characters skilled in image design. This is important because SWG is like Firiona Vie with a single character per server (SCS) limit. You can have up to 10 characters per account, they just have to be on different servers. Rerolli Marr will not have the same power there as she does here.<br>
<br>
The wilderness is vast and amazingly beautiful. I love just walking or sitting in the waving grass of the plains, watching the clouds chase the moons of Naboo across the sky. Little butterflies and bugs scatter from the flora as you walk by and the water ripples with the wind or a fish. Near to cities you can hear and see shuttles and other air cars flying overhead. A rainstorm sounds and feels like a rainstorm, and you can get lost in a dust storm on Tattoine if you are not watching your map.<br>
<br>
The world is definitely designed with personal vehicles in mind. The wilderness is huge, and I use the shuttle system exclusively to move between cities since personal vehicles will not be available for a while after launch. Walking in the wilds is beautiful, but I find myself spending too much time watching my radar for threats, and not enough being allowed to enjoy the walk. I am with Mal in that I WANT to be affected by the terrain. I should want to use mountain passes or avoid a swamp, and I dont like being able to walk up sheer cliffs or run down them with no concerns of damage. Right now I can just set my direction and turn on auto run, and only wildlife adds will keep me from reaching my destination. Ugh.<br>
<br>
I miss roads and paths outside of towns. The towns feel like they were air dropped down at one location and are not really part of the landscape. Many towns are almost medieval because just about everything resides inside of a set of town walls. The towns also suffer from a problem like what I saw in AO. Lots of buildings, but most do not have a reason for being there other than keeping me from walking directly to my destination. Because most people stick to the towns when not on a specific mission, they are also the most laggy places in the world. <br>
<br>
The crafting classes/skills/experience balance need a LOT of work. Many of the advanced crafting skills have basically not been tested to any degree much less balanced. This is made more worrisome because it will not take a huge amount of time to unlock those advanced skills. If it took 2 months for someone to become a novice weaponsmith, then I would be less worried because they will have a little time to work on these after launch. I believe as it stands now, I can solo get novice weaponsmith over the course of a long day (10 hours). Master weaponsmith might take me the rest of a week to finish. Even a small guild will be able to power train their crafting characters much quicker than that.<br>
<br>
There are no real tactics currently for combat. Solo combat is balanced ok, in that you will tend to get incapacitated by a white con mob (even) about 50% of the time, and the various special moves will allow you to do more than just whack-a-mole. The experience for groups though is much higher; too high in my opinion as in a group you can max out a marksman branch in an hour and be about half way to advanced mastership after a day. The maximum group size is 20, and with that many people you can take a bunch of total newbies and zerg just about anything on the starting worlds. No tactics, no strategy, and therefore not much fun for me. The combat power curve is just too shallow for my comfort right now. I do not get more hit points or become substantially more powerful as I attain higher skill levels, and therefore SWG can not ratchet up the mob power so that the newbie zerg group will properly get wiped.<br>
<br>
The economy is supposed to be largely player driven. Right now about 75% of all cash coming into the economy is from players doing missions, with most of the rest being dropped by humanoid NPCs. Unlike EQ quests these missions are quite simple; deliver a package from point A to point B, or go and destroy some lair not far outside of town. The global bazaar needs work before it will before it is even the equivalent of what EQ has in its bazaar. One bright point is that there are decent drains for cash as well. Using the shuttle costs credits, maintaining your house or harvesters takes credits, your gear will decay with use unless you get it repaired and/or buy new gear, and skill training can cost credits if you are not part of a guild.<br>
<br>
Well I have rambled long enough. I would sum up by saying that there is a LOT of potential to this game. I really wish they had allowed themselves time to get the details right. Because they are rushing it out now, I worry about the inertia that will build up behind the current flawed systems which will keep them from ever actually fixing things. Paying customers hate nerfs a hole lot more than beta testers, and customers are always much harder to say no to.<br>
<br>
I am going to give it a try but I am less excited than I was a few months ago. One nice thing is that there is already a good large RP community organized to effectively take over two of the servers (Starsider and Sunrunner), so if you decide to take a look please do drop in and say hello. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perramas>Perramas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/21/03 1:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1680.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Loc of Jedi Temple</span><hr size=1> For those interested the  Jedi Temple is at 4154, 5254 on Dantooine <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=1680.topic&start=21&stop=31>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=1680.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=1680.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1680.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.threadControl?topicID=1680.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?to